TITLE: Defining Custom Animation Types for Moti in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines types and interfaces for custom animations in the Moti library. It includes types for animation properties and a custom animation definition called 'shimmer'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nandorojo/moti/blob/master/docs/docs/animations-sequence.md#2025-04-15_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import type { MotiTransition } from '@motify/core'

export interface AnimationConfig {
  from: {
    opacity?: number
    scale?: number
    translateY?: number
  }
  to: {
    opacity?: number
    scale?: number
    translateY?: number
  }
  transition?: MotiTransition
}

export type Variant = 'shimmer'

export interface CustomAnimationConfig {
  shimmer: AnimationConfig
}

declare module '@motify/core' {
  interface MotiAnimationProp {
    preset?: Variant
  }
}
```

